brief_title: Family-Based Nutrition Intervention for Latino Children
summary:
- Hypothesis: Children whose mothers receive the FBC sessions will have significantly lower BMI one year after the intervention compared to control group children whose families receive an active placebo control.
- Outcome: Mean Change in Body Mass Index (BMI) after 12 months.
- Outcome matched the hypothesis.

- Hypothesis: Adding beneficial high fiber foods to the diet will result in better overall dietary quality than either reducing saturated fat or a combination of high fiber and low saturated fat.
- Outcome: Dietary Quality measured by the Alternate Healthy Eating Index (AHEI) after 6 months.
- Outcome matched the hypothesis.

brief_title: Nutrition, Inflammation and Insulin Resistance in End Stage Renal Disease-Aim 2
lead_sponsor: VA Office of Research and Development
summary:
- Hypothesis: Inhibiting inflammatory response or increasing insulin sensitivity will improve net protein metabolism in hemodialysis patients.
- Primary Outcome: Change in Leucine Disposal Rate (LDR) after 3 months.
- Secondary Outcome: Change in Whole-body Net Protein Balance and Skeletal Muscle Net Protein Balance after 3 months.
- Outcome parameters matched the hypothesis.

Study 4: Omega-3 for Depression and Other Cardiac Risk Factors-2

brief_title: Omega-3 for Depression and Other Cardiac Risk Factors - 2
summary:
- Hypothesis: Antidepressant augmentation with EPA omega-3 is superior to antidepressant therapy alone for major depression in patients with coronary heart disease (CHD).
- Primary Outcome: Beck Depression Inventory-II (BDI-II) score change after 10 weeks.
- Secondary Outcome: Hamilton Depression Rating Scale (HAM-D, 17) score change after 10 weeks.
- Outcome parameters matched the hypothesis.
